<DOC><DOCNO> AP900705-0086 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-05-90 1328EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-BRF--BoilingDeath     07-05 0085</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Boiling Death,0086</SECOND><HEAD>Housemate Charged in Scalding Death</HEAD><DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man has been charged with murder in thedeath of his housemate, who was scalded with boiling water after anargument over a pack of cigarettes, authorities said.   Thomas Wright, 47, was scalded May 22 after he fell asleepfollowing the argument, investigators said.   Odell Butler, 57, originally was charged with aggravated assaultbut the charge was changed to second-degree murder after Wrightdied Monday at a Memphis hospital, authorities said.</TEXT></DOC>